title: For Sale:  1953 Vintage and very clean SKS Russian made AK47
postcontent: Well I was at the the Loveland gun show and fell in love with an Arsenal AK47. I had to have it. I was toting around my Russian made SKS 7.62x39mm which got a lot of attention. At the time I did not want to sell it. This gun is milled so it is extremely accurate at 100-150 yards. Its curtains for any animal on all fours with this hell fire round. Gun bore is shiny as any BRAND new barrel. It's been well taken care of. No pitting or any rust for that matter. All serial numbers match from butt stock to barrel. Dealer offered me 750.00 at the gun show. Like I said I wasn't ready to sell earlier. Not until I took the hit when I checked my balance. Don't get me wrong I am not hurting but got to explain Momma where the money went if I don't sell my ever so reliable and extremely clean SKS all Russian. Not a Chinese piece of junk. Sorry Norinko fans. I will let this gun go for 750.00 firm. Pretty soon this wont be available, not for this price. At the gun show they were selling ones in worse shape for 1200.00. That is highway robbery if you ask me. Anyway I think in todays environment with prices for these gun just going up. 750.00 is an honest and fair price for this all russian made beauty. Made by Tula in Russia. It is so cool cause it's got russian writing all over it. Adds flavor to an awesome rifle. Gives you some wiggle room to add new furniture if you want. If I were you I would keep it just the way it is. Eats rounds flawlessly. Gonna protect in times of need. I would choose this rather than a Wasr 10/63 anyday. Plus for a lot less too. Hit me up if your interested. Setup for the quick sale. Must have valid ID and not be a felon. First 750.00 gets it. Oh it has all the original cleaning kits with original bayonet with original military green strap. Barrel is hammer forged and chrome so this will eat any ammo corrosive or non corrosive. Photos enclosed. Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  LWRCI M6A2 PISTON CARBINE 14.7" barrel w/flash hider; New in Box
postcontent:
I have a LWRCI M6A2 carbine for sale.  It's brand new, in the factory box and still sealed in the factory sleeve.  This is the best of the best when it comes to AR-15 style rifles.  The 14.7" barrel has a factory flash hider installed which brings it to legal length: it is not a SBR.

Caliber: 5.56 NATO
Barrel Length: 14.7" plus A2 birdcage Muzzle Device 1/2x28 TPI (5.56)
Weight (unloaded): approximately 7.2 lbs 
Length (overall): 31.9" - 35.1" (14.7” barrel)
Rate of Fire: Semi-Auto or Select Fire 700 rpm (+/- 100 rpm)
Rifling: 1/7" RH (5.56)
Stock/Pistol Grip: B5 Systems SOPMOD/Magpul MIAD
Sights: LWRCI Folding BUIS Front and Rear
Magazine: Magpul 30 rd. P-Mag (5.56)

The M6A2™ rifle is ideal for those who utilize optical sights as it employs a low- profile gas block. There is no A-frame front sight to obscure the field of view of the optical device. The M6A2™ rifle also features a longer midlength free float rail system with a removable return-to-zero top. Any M4 MIL Std 1913 accessory can be mounted to the rail, and because the rail has a monolithic profile, you can bridge devices from the receiver to the rail seamlessly. The longer rail also affords more 1913 “real estate” to mount your accessories.

The M6A2™ rifle with the 14.7 inch barrel is an excellent general purpose carbine capable of effective fire out to 600+ meters.

The M6A2™ rifle’s edge in capability, reliability, accuracy and long service life is the result of advanced technology materials and manufacturing processes, combined with progressive patented designs.

LWRCI™ has engineered a complete solution to the deficits found in the direct impingement M16/AR15/M4 family of rifles and carbines. All LWRCI™ carbine systems feature a patented short-stroke gas-piston operating system. The operating system is lightweight, self-regulating, and self-scraping. This system of operation does not foul the moving parts of the weapon with carbon or heat, because it eliminates the venting of hot, carbon-laden gases into the receiver and bolt carrier group, thus eliminating the intensive cleaning regime of the legacy rifle. It also means the bolt carrier group and associated springs are not subjected to the searing heat of the tapped gasses, this being one of the major causes of small parts failure. This translates into carbines that are far more reliable than the legacy direct impingement carbines regardless of user maintenance, greatly enhancing service life and reliability while decreasing the need for both user and armorer maintenance.

Another benefit of the LWRC short-stroke gas-piston system is the improved handling characteristics of our weapons over the direct impingement legacy weapons. Recoil is lighter and muzzle rise is greatly reduced. Amazingly, this is accomplished in a carbine that is ergonomically identical, weighs almost the same, and retains 80% parts commonality with the legacy direct impingement carbine.

All LWRCI M6A2™ rifles feature a match grade, cold rotary hammer forged barrel with a target crown, made from 41V45 steel alloy blanks. Cold hammer forging takes an oversized barrel blank, and using high pressure rotary hammers, compacts the barrel blank over a mandrel. This forms perfect rifling without any tool marks. It also compacts the molecular structure of the metal making it denser and stronger. These barrels can take a lot more use and abuse than a standard barrel before any degradation in accuracy or loss of velocity.  After forming, the barrels are treated with NiCorr™ surface conversion technology. vNiCorr™ surface conversion has proved more lubricious, harder wearing, more heat and corrosion resistant than the hard chrome normally used in the bore. LWRC barrels can handle 20,000 rounds before replacement, as compared to 6,000-10,000 rounds on a standard M4. The NiCorr™ surface conversion technology extends service life, enhances accuracy, and increases the effective range of the weapon.

The bolt carrier group and the barrel extension of the LWRC M6A2 rifle is coated with EXO’s patented nickel-boron surface conversion technology that provides a hard permanent lubrication to the moving parts. The nickel-boron surface conversion nearly eliminates corrosion while providing greatly increased lubricity. This nickel coating is similar to that being used by the US Army Research Lab and USSOCOM to extend the service life of their weapons systems.

The M6A2™ rifle is the most modern and incrementally evolved carbine in the world. At the same time it also presents the best value. Service life is extended to four times that of a legacy M4, accuracy is 100 percent better, and LWRC’s M6 rifles are many times more reliable than the legacy gas-impingement design.

title: For Sale:  1944 Finnish Sako Mosin Nagant
postcontent: I have (1) 1944 Finnish Sako Mosin Nagant with a hex reciever in excellent condition. Reciever looks to be originally of French origin and has no date stamp under tang so it is a very early French receiver. All matching numbers minus hinged floor plate, which is common for Finnish rearsenals. Incredible shooter with strong and bright rifling. Has no chamber or throat erosion. Bolt manipulation is almost effort less and has a beautiful trigger for being a military rifle of its age. Wooden stock and metal fittings are in great/nearly new condition. Will come with (1) green original Sako leather sling, roughly 500 rounds of 7.62 x 54r, (1) original brass muzzle protector, (1) screwdriver/firing pin guage. Not in any rush to sell this old girl, just hoping to find her a good home where she'll be appreciated as I just don't have the time or space in my collection. Price is firm but am willing to negotiate if I know its going to someone who will take care of her and preserve the original conition. Will consider trade for a Remington R1 1911 or anything comparable.
